GrwMnd_Dur:
Growth mindset is about having the confidence and the risk-taker attitude to grow yourself as a person - in every which way - your personality, your skills, the knowledge you hold, your intelligence level, your qualities and the positivity in your attitude.

People can range between fixed mindedness and growth mindedness. For instance, some might believe the intelligence someone is born with cannot be altered while someone might believe that hard working and passion for something, to grow one's knowledge and learning can actually impact their intelligence.

Growth mindedness is all about thinking about the fact that no one is perfect. One who follows this shouldn't worry about making mistakes, after all no one is born perfect. Speaking out what you feel, hearing arguments and considering your firm beliefs, reflecting of wise words is all about having a growth mindset.
